Mutex Debounce Pattern: 
Use an 'isStarting' flag or a Map of locks to track active async operations. 
Example:
if (this.locks.has(id)) return Promise.resolve(this.locks.get(id));
const promise = (async () => { ... })();
this.locks.set(id, promise);
try { return await promise; } finally { this.locks.delete(id); }

Optimistic Locking Pattern: 
Include a 'version' or 'updatedAt' field in the document. 
Example:
const doc = await db.get(id);
if (doc.updatedAt !== localUpdatedAt) throw new Error('Document modified by another tenant');
await db.set(id, { ...newData, updatedAt: Date.now() });
